Optimisation of the transfection method resulted in transfection efficiencies averaging 30% (Fig. 2
). Helper cell line clones (CRFK/tas) were developed over a 5-month period, with cell clones being grown to confluency, expanded, tested and frozen as stocks. Thirty-two CRFK/tas single cell clones were identified. Seven of these clones were found to express functional Tas, with efficiencies ranging from 25–60% (Fig. 3
).
